FBIS4-54111 "dreas101_d_94016" FBIS-EAS-94-101 Daily Report 24 May 1994 South Korea Environment Minister To Attend UN Conference Environment Minister To Attend UN Conference SK2405004994 Seoul THE KOREA TIMES in English 24 May 94 p 3 SK2405004994 Seoul THE KOREA TIMES English BFN [Text] Environment Minister Pak Yun-hun will leave for New York today to attend the three-day conference of the U.N. Commission on Sustainable Development (CSD) which begins Wednesday. Pak, chief of the Korean delegation to the international forum, will speak on Korea's role and commitment in the environmental context and promise financial support for underdeveloped countries while calling for a transfer of clean technology from advanced countries. The conference will be attended by 53 CSD member countries, the U.N. Environment Program, General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade (GATT) and other non-governmental organizations. The participants will discuss implementing of Agenda 21 adopted at the U.N. conference on environment and development in Rio de Janeiro in 1992. The Korean delegation includes 11 officials from the Economic Planning Board, Foreign and Environment Ministries, and two non- governmental experts.
